WEBVTT

00:00.067 --> 00:02.000
Previously on Ghost Whisperer.

00:02.000 --> 00:04.500
You move between the world of life and death.

00:04.500 --> 00:06.667
You don't know the price.

00:06.734 --> 00:08.234
What price?

00:09.567 --> 00:12.367
No! please, not you!

00:12.434 --> 00:13.634
You have to cross over.

00:13.701 --> 00:15.000
I don't want to.

00:15.301 --> 00:17.500
I saw Jim's ghost step into Sam's body.

00:19.401 --> 00:20.467
You're back!

00:20.467 --> 00:21.767
Do I know you?

00:21.767 --> 00:23.501
I see the same guy that you see,

00:23.502 --> 00:26.135
Different hair, nose, eyes. It's not Jim.

00:26.202 --> 00:27.801
He's in there somewhere.

00:27.868 --> 00:28.801
He just has to be.

00:28.801 --> 00:29.801
You're not gonna tell me that

00:29.801 --> 00:31.101
you think I'm your husband reincarnated.

00:31.168 --> 00:34.035
Because your are the only sane person I've met since I woke up.

00:34.101 --> 00:36.701
It's not much. But maybe you could help me finish my garage.

00:36.768 --> 00:38.202
And you could live there while you do the work.

00:38.268 --> 00:40.035
Just until you figure out your next move.

00:40.101 --> 00:42.035
That's strange. I've been hoping for a clue.

00:42.101 --> 00:43.801
Something to tell me who I was.

00:43.868 --> 00:45.569
I bought that less than a month ago.

00:45.635 --> 00:48.368
Question is, who did I buy it for?

00:48.435 --> 00:49.801
Sam?

00:49.801 --> 00:52.302
Oh, my god. It's true. You don't know who I am, do you?

00:52.368 --> 00:53.535
You must be Nicole.

00:53.602 --> 00:54.301
The fiance?

00:54.301 --> 00:56.802
She is not his fiance until he puts a ring on her finger.

01:00.602 --> 01:02.535
Ok. So where are they now?

01:02.602 --> 01:04.168
I don't know. He hasn't been home all day.

01:04.235 --> 01:06.635
But he's with her? Nikki.

01:06.701 --> 01:07.834
I assume so.

01:07.901 --> 01:10.135
How much time are they actually spending together?

01:10.202 --> 01:13.135
Well, he's not working, and she's in town. so...

01:13.202 --> 01:15.435
You didn't tell me they were spending whole days together.

01:15.502 --> 01:18.168
What about the nights? Is she still staying at the hotel?

01:18.235 --> 01:19.268
Yes.

01:19.335 --> 01:22.468
But they're spending all day together.

01:22.535 --> 01:24.768
I'm really trying not to think about it.

01:24.834 --> 01:26.669
I thought he was just trying to get in touch with her

01:26.734 --> 01:28.251
So that he could explain to her what happened

01:28.251 --> 01:29.768
and then say goodbye.

01:29.834 --> 01:32.035
Well, guess what. They're saying hello.

01:33.135 --> 01:35.268
I think I hear them.

01:35.335 --> 01:38.935
No. No. No. They're just gonna see you.

01:39.001 --> 01:40.768
Oh, yeah. That's a lot better.

01:40.834 --> 01:42.701
Did she see me?

01:42.768 --> 01:43.701
Can I?

01:43.768 --> 01:45.535
- No. - Hold on a second, Sam.

01:45.602 --> 01:47.768
Uh, Melinda?

01:47.834 --> 01:48.935
This is nuts.

01:49.001 --> 01:50.302
Hi. I am Delia.

01:50.368 --> 01:51.602
Hi, Delia. I'm Nikki.

01:51.669 --> 01:53.901
I was looking for Melinda.

01:53.968 --> 01:55.801
- Found it!  -Oh, gosh!

01:58.801 --> 02:02.168
Nikki, Delia. Have you met Delia?

02:02.235 --> 02:03.801
Yes. We did.

02:03.868 --> 02:05.301
- I found it.  - Oh, great.

02:05.301 --> 02:07.468
I'm so sorry we had to come all the way back here for just this.

02:07.535 --> 02:09.768
No. It's great.

02:09.834 --> 02:11.435
Hey, Melinda.

02:11.502 --> 02:14.502
Hi, Sam.

02:14.569 --> 02:16.301
Uh, Nikki left her cell phone here. So...

02:16.301 --> 02:18.468
Right. So...

02:18.535 --> 02:19.868
I guess I'll be taking you back...

02:19.935 --> 02:21.569
Well, actually that's why I wanted talk to you.

02:21.635 --> 02:24.268
Melinda, the hotel that I booked is really nice.

02:24.335 --> 02:25.402
It's fine and everything.

02:25.468 --> 02:27.168
But I'm actually going to be spending

02:27.235 --> 02:29.834
a little bit more time than I originally planned.

02:29.991 --> 02:32.659
And I really want to help Sam out as much as possible.

02:32.725 --> 02:35.125
But I was only able to get a week off from work.

02:35.191 --> 02:37.991
And I don't want to waste a minute that I could spend with him.

02:38.058 --> 02:41.592
So, you are here. And just if you didn't mind?

02:41.659 --> 02:43.158
Mind?

02:43.225 --> 02:46.458
Just 'cause obviously I couldn't stay with Sam.

02:46.525 --> 02:47.924
Obviously.

02:47.991 --> 02:49.791
No. No.

02:49.858 --> 02:51.592
Because we're really just getting to know each other.

02:51.659 --> 02:54.791
Yeah. Yeah. Of course.

02:54.858 --> 02:58.058
Really? It's ok. I can stay with you?

02:59.025 --> 02:59.958
Sure.

03:00.025 --> 03:01.500
- Great.  - Great.

03:01.958 --> 03:02.992
Great.

03:05.824 --> 03:07.758
We were walking around the house into the back.

03:07.758 --> 03:09.692
And we get there.

03:09.759 --> 03:12.392
And her grandmother and grandfather are there.

03:12.458 --> 03:14.325
Oh, my god!

03:18.458 --> 03:19.759
What are you doing?

03:19.824 --> 03:21.058
Swimming.

03:21.325 --> 03:23.158
Are you crazy? What are you thinking?

03:23.325 --> 03:25.025
Paula, come on, it's freezing!

03:25.092 --> 03:26.698
No way!

03:26.698 --> 03:28.125
She's going in.

03:28.125 --> 03:29.525
- No.  - Catch me if you can!

03:29.591 --> 03:30.891
Paula, don't go out there.

03:30.958 --> 03:32.425
Oh, my God! This is noÂ£Â¡

03:33.858 --> 03:34.991
Is she serious?

03:34.991 --> 03:36.191
I'm not going in there, no way!

03:36.191 --> 03:37.191
Paula, come back!

03:37.191 --> 03:38.191
Mark, do something.

03:38.191 --> 03:40.875
Paula, come on! Wait!

03:40.875 --> 03:43.559
Paula, come on! It's freezing.

03:43.624 --> 03:46.559
Seriously, come on!

